				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(637830); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=637830&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227467" alt="SoullessSingularity" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=637830)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(637830); return false;" >SoullessSingularity</a></span> <span class="odate time_1521935324 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Mar 2018 23:48</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3748679">
									

<p>1. I really like the general arc going for it and feel it has serious emotional weight.</p>
<p>2. I could not get over the lack of placement of characters in any subscene, nor the fact that each subscene did not have its own structure. This piece is a string of vignettes that tries to become a story, but no vignettes themselves have a story structure, and thus it falls flat for me overall. It is difficult to emotionally bond with silhouettes and talking heads in a void, and in which we only hear snippets of their conversation disjointedly over time.</p>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>Living the dream, or dreaming the life?</p>

				</div>
					
					
